nodes.title: Important
widgets_values: If you have RAM | VRAM issue, it's recommended to bypass Video Combine and use Save Images.
Use t2v 1.3B fp32/bf16/fp16 as the refinement model. Enable Torch Compile Mode Wan Video to speed up about 15%~25%.

nodes.title: Triton
widgets_values:
Wan Video Torch Compile Settings is disconnected by default and will not take effect if you're using fp8 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx.

If you choose t2v 1.3B fp32/bf16/fp16 model, then you can:
1. Link Wan Video Torch Compile Settings to the Wan Video Model Loader to speed up about 15%~25%..
2. Follow the VRAM settings instruction in the Wan Video Wrapper Tips Group.

nodes.type: CR Apply LoRA Stack Model Only JK

properties.Node name for S&R: CR Apply LoRA Stack Model Only JK

widgets_values:
(default) bypass Torch Compile Mode Wan Video if you're using fp8 diffusion model and your graphic card is 20xx or 30xx.

If you choose t2v 1.3B fp32/bf16/fp16 model, then you can change weight_dtype to default, change Wan Video TeaCache coefficients to 1.3B and link Torch Compile Mode Wan Video to the workflow to speed up about 15%~25%.

nodes.title: lora
widgets_values:
14B speedup lora doesn't support 1.3B main model

merge_loras off:
Same result for using WanVideo Set LoRAs Node or linking directly to lora slot of WanVideo Model Loder.

merge_loras on:
is only for linking directly to the lora slot of the WanVideo Model Loader and achieves a different (maybe better) result from merge_loras off.

Tune lora and lora str:
Use WanVideo Set LoRAs Node and turn off merge_loras without loading main model repeatly.

Fixed lora and test merge_loras on:
link directly to lora slot of WanVideo Model Loder and turn on merge_loras.

It's recommended to bypass TeaCache | MegaCache | EasyCache and SLG nodes when using speed up lora.

nodes.title: Dilated ControlNet
widgets_values:
For Wan1.3B model controlnet:
  blocks count = 8 and stride = 3
For Wan14B model controlnet:
  blocks count = 6 and stride = 4
Remember to enable "Load Single Control Video" group.

choose sparse sage attention:
select sageatten in the Model Loder and bypass the Set Radial Attention.
choose radial sage attention:
select radial_sage_attention in the Model Loder and select sageatten in the Set Radial Attention.

The speed of Radial SageAttn is faster than the Sparse SageAttn.
Sage Attention might cause artifacts while upscaling the video.

you can load depth lora or fun control video from:

1. Video (Load Video Node)
2. Images from disk (Load Images From Folder Node)
3. Webp Animate Image (Load Image Node)

Control Video for:
 t2v depth lora control
 t2v|i2v fun control (multi types)
 uniAnimate pose control

Bypass KJ TeaCache and SLG nodes if they causes errors or artifacts especially when using t2v 1.3B. And choose native SLG instead.

Bypass KJ TeaCache and SLG nodes when using speed up lora.
